Heh, sorry for all the questions, this is a new subject to me.  Thanks for the help. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udracillionofqeynos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DracillionofQeynos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 12:39:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1356.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: how soon?</span><hr size=1> I would definately do Run3 first.  Its a bit slower or equal to Jboots and faster than TBoots.  Its always on and works in doors.  Indespensible.<br>
<br>
For the next, its kind of up to you.  I'm going to put mine into regen because I figure a little extra regen can't hurt, especially if you solo a bit.  The bind wound one would not be bad either as that would let you bind to 100% if your over level 57 and have Bind Wound over 201.<br>
<br>
You get AA abilities at 51.  I believe you can only do general ones until 55 when you can put points into arch.  You can't put points into class ones until level 59.  <br>
<br>
You have to manually decide how much xp goes to aa and to regular xp.  You can access the alt adv button when you hit your inventory screen.  You can click on each of then, and it will tell you what they do.  <br>
<br>
Before level 60, you may want to put points and get to Run3.  Besides that though, I'd get to 60 before I put any experience into alternate advancement.   <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=127089">Dracillion of Qeynos</a>
